'''Shyster''' may refer to:

* ([[description]]) A '''shyster''' is an unscrupulous person, especially in the practice of law and politics, or a [[con artist]]. The word probably originated from German ''Scheisser'' - "incompetent worthless person," literally "defecator". This term has been used in Isaac Asimov's short science-fiction robot story "Evidence". An atmosphere is created around a falsity and then proven wrong.
* ([[military]]) '''SS-3 Shyster''' is the [[NATO reporting name]] for the [[R-5]] [[theatre ballistic missile]].

